1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a method for localising and estimating the dimensions of objects using RGB cameras, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed method can be applied to robotic systems for object manipulation and grasping, making this sub-category a likely fit. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the proposed method does not rely on deep learning, it involves iterative shape fitting and image re-projection, which can be considered as machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves intelligent processing of visual information to estimate object properties, which falls under the scope of AI research. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper involves the estimation of object dimensions from images, which can be considered as a graphics-related problem.
